62.8	Robertson_Davies	Robertson Davies	William Robertson Davies, CC, OOnt, FRSC, FRSL (August 28, 1913 â€“ December 2, 1995) was a Canadian novelist, playwright, critic, journalist, and professor. He was one of Canada's best-known and most popular authors, and one of its most distinguished "men of letters", a term Davies is variously said to have gladly accepted for himself and to have detested. Davies was the founding Master of Massey College, a graduate residential college associated with the University of Toronto.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/RobertsonDavies.jpg/220px-RobertsonDavies.jpg
